messages.message:
I really like the new UX for table -- the flat spreadsheet-like interface is much more generalizable, and also gives potentially inline editing capability in the future which I guess wasn't possible earlier. Good job!!! Makes it look much more sleek.

In the AI tooling -- UX will play the most critical part -- so simpler, and more useful the UX is -- more people will love the tool.

Same rendering pattern is used with app review screen and it supports editing.

Good work @Aayush.
